Inspired by Japan’s futuristic Capital, The Tokyo, is a 15 storey residential development coming up at the corner of Longmarket and Loop Street. Also Read: Skyveld Development in Rosebank, Johannesburg, South Africa The development is set to have a total of 148 units of hotel-style living apartments whose size range from 25m2 – 43m2. The apartments have open-plan designs and floor-to-ceiling windows that ensure that their occupants get to enjoy every detail of glowing sunrises and moody sunsets while framing one of Cape Town’s most iconic scenes.  The development features biometric access control & 24hr CCTV surveillance throughout, a restaurant & café on the ground floor, 24hr concierge security, parcel delivery safe holding area, integrated intercom from the foyer to every apartment, a fitness center with changing rooms, a business lounge with high-speed Wi-Fi connectivity, rooftop sunset terrace with a pool and braai areas, fiber & DSTV connectivity and optional air-conditioning. The development is also in close proximity to trendy bars, restaurants, and a myriad of boutique retail destinations, it boasts central access to hotspots like the CBD, Cape Town International Convention Centre, V&A Waterfront, and Table Mountain.  Expected to be completed in May 2023, The Tokyo is developed by Rawson Developers, the property development division of the Rawson Property Group, which is a nationwide property organization founded back in 1982.